regation case","body":"Berry v. School District of the City of Benton Harbor began in the 1970s and wound through the federal courts for decades. Hillman took over the case, issued a comprehensive remedial order in 1981 mandating compensatory education, busing adjustments, and faculty diversification — rejecting inter-district mergers as too disruptive.","number":2},{"header":"He co-founded the World Affairs Council of Western","body":"In 1949, just two years after passing the bar, Douglas Hillman co-founded the World Affairs Council of Western Michigan alongside businessman Edgar Orr. Their mission was to heighten global awareness among Americans, with a particular focus on engaging younger generations through lectures and cultural exchange. The Hillman-Orr Award, named jointly for both founders, continues today, honoring regional contributions to international understanding.","number":3}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Chief Judge Douglas Woodruff Hillman","first_name":"Douglas","last_name":"Hillman","middle_name":"Woodruff","title":"Chief Judge","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"douglas-hillman-1922"},"neighborhood":{"focus":{"id":"HD2502","slug":"douglas-hillman-1922","n":"Chief Judge Douglas Woodruff Hillman","by":1922,"dy":2007,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":11},"spouses":[{"order":1,"spouse":{"id":"X00826","slug":"sarah-jones-1923","n":"Sarah Adelaide Jones Hillman","by":1923,"dy":2013,"sx":"f","hd":false,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":null},"year":1944,"children":[{"id":"HD3139","slug":"drusilla-hillman","n":"Drusilla Hillman","by":null,"dy":null,"sx":"f","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":12},{"id":"HD2508","slug":"clayton-hillman-1956","n":"Clayton Douglas Hillman","by":1956,"dy":1996,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":12}]}],"parents":{"father":{"id":"X00822"